Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.84,0:02:23.25,辉注,,0,0,0,,接下来是片头与工商时间 正片空降坐标2:20
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.88,0:04:05.42,辉注,,0,0,0,,"Wet Workshop"空间站,也叫"湿车间",是使用一个废火箭级作为临时空间站的想法.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.16,0:00:03.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们都知道阿波罗计划的主要目标是什么
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.16,0:00:03.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,We all know what the major goal of the Apollo program was,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:03.44,0:00:06.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,就是在60年代末将人类送上月球
Dialogue: 2,0:00:03.44,0:00:06.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,to put a man on the moon by the end of the 1960s
Dialogue: 1,0:00:06.75,0:00:11.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,主要是为了打败苏联人 证明所谓"资本主义优于共产主义"
Dialogue: 2,0:00:06.75,0:00:11.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,basically to beat the Soviets and prove that the capitalist system was better than the communist one.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:12.24,0:00:15.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,但是等登月成功了 那些已经开发的硬件、火箭、航天器等技术将何去何从?
Dialogue: 2,0:00:12.24,0:00:15.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,But once that's done what would happen the hardware,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:15.27,0:00:19.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,但是等登月成功了 那些已经开发的硬件、火箭、航天器等技术将何去何从?
Dialogue: 2,0:00:15.27,0:00:19.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,the rockets, spacecraft and technology that had been developed,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:19.02,0:00:23.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,更不用说参与到阿波罗工程里的40万名工人
Dialogue: 2,0:00:19.02,0:00:23.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,not to mention the 400,000 workers that helped build them,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:23.92,0:00:27.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果不充分利用他们取得的成果 那阿波罗250亿美元经费就太浪费了
Dialogue: 2,0:00:23.92,0:00:27.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,it would be a waste not to capitalize on gains they had made
Dialogue: 1,0:00:27.23,0:00:31.63,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果不充分利用他们取得的成果 那阿波罗250亿美元经费就太浪费了
Dialogue: 2,0:00:27.23,0:00:31.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,and make the most of the $25 billion that would have been spent.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:31.95,0:00:36.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,为此在1965年 早在第一次登月之前
Dialogue: 2,0:00:31.95,0:00:36.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,To this end in 1965, well before the first moon landing,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:36.33,0:00:42.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,就出现了一个名为"土星阿波罗应用"的计划 后来改为"阿波罗应用计划"
Dialogue: 2,0:00:36.33,0:00:42.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,a program called Saturn Apollo Applications, which later became the Apollo Applications Program
Dialogue: 1,0:00:42.52,0:00:49.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,以在首批登月后利用阿波罗的硬件执行一系列其他任务
Dialogue: 2,0:00:42.52,0:00:49.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,was created to utilise the Apollo hardware for a range of other duties after the initial moon landings,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:49.44,0:00:55.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,因此在本期视频中 我们将看到决策者眼中70年代的阿波罗会怎样大放光芒
Dialogue: 2,0:00:49.44,0:00:55.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,so in this video, we'll look at what the planners thought Apollo might have gone on to do in the 1970s
Dialogue: 1,0:00:55.88,0:00:59.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,以及阿波罗1号的火灾是如何改变一切的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:55.88,0:00:59.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,and how the Apollo 1 fire changed everything.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:23.76,0:02:28.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,阿波罗应用计划是包括韦恩赫尔·冯·布劳恩在内的规划者
Dialogue: 2,0:02:23.76,0:02:28.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Apollo Applications Program was what the planners including Werner Von Bruan
Dialogue: 1,0:02:28.64,0:02:33.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,希望阿波罗计划在完成首批登月之后能够继续发展而想出的
Dialogue: 2,0:02:28.64,0:02:33.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,hoped Apollo would lead on to once the initial moon landing had been completed.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:33.54,0:02:38.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,此时仍是太空探索的早期阶段 如我们之前关于天空实验室的视频中所见
Dialogue: 2,0:02:33.54,0:02:38.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,This was still an early time for space exploration and as we saw in a previous video about Skylab,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:38.84,0:02:45.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们可能已经登上了月球 但我们其实并不知道如何在太空中长期工作生活
Dialogue: 2,0:02:38.84,0:02:45.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,we may well have gone to the moon but we didn't really know how to live and work in space for long periods.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:45.99,0:02:50.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,阿波罗应用计划将利用已经开发的东西
Dialogue: 2,0:02:45.99,0:02:50.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Apollo Applications Program would take what had developed and run with it
Dialogue: 1,0:02:50.10,0:02:54.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,来开发人类不仅在太空中、还能在月球上生活的能力
Dialogue: 2,0:02:50.10,0:02:54.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,to help develop our abilities to not only live in space but also on the moon.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:55.07,0:02:59.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,在1965年 根据资金维持情况有两条可能的路线
Dialogue: 2,0:02:55.07,0:02:59.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,In 1965 there were two possible routes depending on how the funding would hold up.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:00.18,0:03:02.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,第一种情况下
Dialogue: 2,0:03:00.18,0:03:02.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,The first "Case 1" scenario
Dialogue: 1,0:03:02.81,0:03:08.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,登月任务之后将不再订购土星火箭与阿波罗飞船的硬件
Dialogue: 2,0:03:02.81,0:03:08.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,was that there would be no further Saturn Apollo hardware ordered past that of the moon missions.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:08.72,0:03:15.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,即使有这些限制 土星-阿波罗项目组仍认为到1973年底会打21发土星1B
Dialogue: 2,0:03:08.72,0:03:15.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even with these limitations, the Saturn Apollo Office thought there would 21 Saturn 1B launches,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:15.44,0:03:22.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,(土星1B是土星五号没有一级的短版本 火箭是在抬高的支架上发射的
Dialogue: 2,0:03:15.44,0:03:22.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,(that's the shorter version without the main 1st stage that sat on the milk stool launch pad
Dialogue: 1,0:03:22.01,0:03:24.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,用于发射较轻的载荷)
Dialogue: 2,0:03:22.01,0:03:24.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,and would be used for lighter loads)
Dialogue: 1,0:03:24.10,0:03:30.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,到1973年底还有15次全尺寸土星五号的发射
Dialogue: 2,0:03:24.10,0:03:30.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,and 15 full-sized Saturn V launches by the end of 1973.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:31.28,0:03:37.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,第二种情况将极大化利用土星-阿波罗的能力
Dialogue: 2,0:03:31.28,0:03:37.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,The second “Case 2” scenario would see an extensive utilization of Saturn Apollo capabilities,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:37.59,0:03:42.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,会更早地聚焦于"后阿波罗时期"的国家太空目标
Dialogue: 2,0:03:37.59,0:03:42.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,with an earlier focus on a post-Apollo national space objective,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:43.30,0:03:48.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些额外的发射任务将在登月和其他任务之间交错进行
Dialogue: 2,0:03:43.30,0:03:48.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,these extra launches would interleave between the moon landings and other missions.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:48.88,0:03:55.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,包括使用土星五号火箭上面级的燃料箱作为湿车间
Dialogue: 2,0:03:48.88,0:03:55.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,These would include using the fuel tank of the upper stage of a Saturn V rocket as a wet workshop.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:55.78,0:04:01.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,燃料箱中的燃料用完后 剩余的燃料会排放到太空中
Dialogue: 2,0:03:55.78,0:04:01.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once the fuel in the tank was spent, instead of just jettisoning it they would vent any fuel left into space
Dialogue: 1,0:04:01.85,0:04:05.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,然后将内部作为居住舱与湿车间
Dialogue: 2,0:04:01.85,0:04:05.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then use the interior as a habitat and workshop.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:05.84,0:04:08.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,该想法后被用于天空实验室
Dialogue: 2,0:04:05.84,0:04:08.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,This idea would be later used for Skylab,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:08.72,0:04:15.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,虽然那属于"干车间" 因为它是专为任务制造的 从未被用作燃料箱
Dialogue: 2,0:04:08.72,0:04:15.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,though that was a dry workshop as it was purpose-built for the task never used as a fuel tank in space.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:15.76,0:04:18.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,登月计划有四个阶段
Dialogue: 2,0:04:15.76,0:04:18.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,There were four planned phases to the moon landings.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:19.12,0:04:24.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,第一阶段是1969年到1971年 第一批人登陆月球并在四次任务中积累经验
Dialogue: 2,0:04:19.12,0:04:24.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,Phase 1 was from 1969 to 1971 which would land the first men on the moon
Dialogue: 1,0:04:24.77,0:04:27.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,第一阶段是1969年到1971年 第一批人登陆月球并在四次任务中积累经验
Dialogue: 2,0:04:24.77,0:04:27.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,and build up experience over the four missions.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:27.93,0:04:31.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,对应阿波罗11到14号
Dialogue: 2,0:04:27.93,0:04:31.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,These missions corresponded to Apollo 11 to 14.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:32.20,0:04:37.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,第二阶段是1972年到1973年 月球探索阶段
Dialogue: 2,0:04:32.20,0:04:37.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,Phase 2 from 1972 to 1973 would be the Lunar Exploration Phase,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:37.57,0:04:43.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些任务将在月球停留更长的时间 并带来包括月球车在内的更大载荷
Dialogue: 2,0:04:37.57,0:04:43.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,these missions would stay for longer duration and bring larger payloads including the Lunar rover,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:43.63,0:04:47.63,辉中,,0,0,0,,对应阿波罗15到17号
Dialogue: 2,0:04:43.63,0:04:47.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,these ended up corresponding to Apollo 15 to 17.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:47.85,0:04:53.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,第三阶段在1974年进行 是一次月球勘测任务
Dialogue: 2,0:04:47.85,0:04:53.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,Phase 3 was pencilled in for 1974 and was a lunar Oritbal Survey mission
Dialogue: 1,0:04:54.03,0:04:58.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,有点像阿波罗8号 但只有两名宇航员 而不是三名
Dialogue: 2,0:04:54.03,0:04:58.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,which would be a bit like Apollo 8 but with two astronauts instead of 3
Dialogue: 1,0:04:58.75,0:05:02.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,而且只有指令舱和服务舱 没有登月舱
Dialogue: 2,0:04:58.75,0:05:02.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,and with just the Command and Service Module without the Lunar Module.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:02.72,0:05:06.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,飞船将进入月球极地轨道飞行28天
Dialogue: 2,0:05:02.72,0:05:06.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,This would enter a polar orbit around the moon for 28 days
Dialogue: 1,0:05:06.92,0:05:13.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,利用胶片相机 磁力计 雷达测高仪 伽马射线光谱仪与服务舱中的微陨石收集板
Dialogue: 2,0:05:06.92,0:05:13.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,and observe the whole surface of the moon with a suite of instruments including film cameras, a magnetometer,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:13.78,0:05:21.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,等一整套设备仪器观察整个月球表面
Dialogue: 2,0:05:13.78,0:05:21.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,a radar altimeter, a gamma-ray spectrometer, and micrometeoroid collection plates in the Service Module.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:21.74,0:05:24.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,这项工作最终交由月球勘测轨道飞行器(LRO)来完成
Dialogue: 2,0:05:21.74,0:05:24.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,This job would eventually be done in much greater detail
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.12,0:05:33.08,辉注,,0,750,950,,{\fs60}月球勘测轨道飞行器
Dialogue: 1,0:05:24.98,0:05:29.04,辉中,,0,0,170,,勘测细节更丰富 持续时间更长
Dialogue: 2,0:05:24.98,0:05:29.04,辉英,,0,0,140,,and for much longer by the Lunar Reconnaissance Orbiter robotic probe
Dialogue: 1,0:05:29.04,0:05:33.08,辉中,,0,0,170,,且从2009年开始持续至今
Dialogue: 2,0:05:29.04,0:05:33.08,辉英,,0,0,140,,starting in 2009 and is still going today.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:33.57,0:05:40.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,第四阶段是1975年到1976年 为月球表面会合与探索阶段
Dialogue: 2,0:05:33.57,0:05:40.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,Phase 4 would be from 1975 to 1976 and would be the Lunar Surface Rendezvous and Exploration Phase
Dialogue: 1,0:05:40.65,0:05:42.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,包括一组两次发射的任务
Dialogue: 2,0:05:40.65,0:05:42.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,and would consist of a dual launch mission.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:43.22,0:05:48.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,一次发射将向月球表面发送一艘改装的月球有效载荷舱(LPM)
Dialogue: 2,0:05:43.22,0:05:48.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,The first would deliver a modified Lunar Payload Module or LPM to the surface of the moon,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:49.04,0:05:54.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,本质是一个登月舱 但没有上升发动机与相关部件及燃料箱
Dialogue: 2,0:05:49.04,0:05:54.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,basically a Lunar Module but without the ascent engines and associated parts and fuel tanks
Dialogue: 1,0:05:54.77,0:06:00.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,使其具有更大的运输食物和科学设备的能力
Dialogue: 2,0:05:54.77,0:06:00.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,to give it a greater payload capability including food and scientific equipment.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:00.63,0:06:05.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,并将作为宇航员在3个月后到达的住所
Dialogue: 2,0:06:00.63,0:06:05.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,This would act as a shelter for when the astronauts arrived up to 3 months later.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:06.00,0:06:09.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,任务的第二部分就是把宇航员送到那 着陆在第一发的登月舱附近
Dialogue: 2,0:06:06.00,0:06:09.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,The second part of the mission would be when the astronauts arrived
Dialogue: 1,0:06:09.52,0:06:12.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,任务的第二部分就是把宇航员送到那 着陆在第一发的登月舱附近
Dialogue: 2,0:06:09.52,0:06:12.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,and would land them near the Lunar Module Shelter,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:12.86,0:06:16.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,之后任务将在月表停留长达14天
Dialogue: 2,0:06:12.86,0:06:16.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,the mission would then stay on the surface for up to 14 days.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:17.36,0:06:23.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,根据设想 这些经过一段时间的建设将发展成一个月球基地
Dialogue: 2,0:06:17.36,0:06:23.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,It was envisioned that over time this basic setup would evolve into a lunar base
Dialogue: 1,0:06:23.20,0:06:26.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,有更大的居住舱 且由核反应堆提供动力
Dialogue: 2,0:06:23.20,0:06:26.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,with larger shelters powered by a nuclear reactor
Dialogue: 1,0:06:26.48,0:06:33.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,有长途月球车 最多可容纳6人一次停留半年
Dialogue: 2,0:06:26.48,0:06:33.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,with long-range rovers and up to 6 men staying for 6 months or 180 days at a time.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:33.60,0:06:37.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,另一个计划是用土星五号载人飞越金星
Dialogue: 2,0:06:33.60,0:06:37.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Another plan was a manned flypast of Venus
Dialogue: 1,0:06:37.04,0:06:43.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,用土星五号送搭载三人乘组的指令舱与服务舱
Dialogue: 2,0:06:37.04,0:06:43.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,with a Saturn V used to send a three-man crew which would flypast in the Command and Service Module
Dialogue: 1,0:06:43.17,0:06:46.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,和土星1B火箭的二级燃料箱对接 完成飞跃
Dialogue: 2,0:06:43.17,0:06:46.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,attached to the second stage fuel tank of a Saturn 1B.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:47.04,0:06:48.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,二级的燃料用光后
Dialogue: 2,0:06:47.04,0:06:48.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once the fuel had been used,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:48.81,0:06:53.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,燃料箱会作为供乘员在分离返回地球前居住的湿车间使用
Dialogue: 2,0:06:48.81,0:06:53.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,the tank would be used as a wet workshop where the crew live on the return journey
Dialogue: 1,0:06:53.49,0:06:55.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,燃料箱会作为供乘员在分离返回地球前居住的湿车间使用
Dialogue: 2,0:06:53.49,0:06:55.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,before separating and returning to Earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:56.07,0:07:00.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,但这些阿波罗应用计划的任务取决于资金的多少
Dialogue: 2,0:06:56.07,0:07:00.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,But these Apollo Application Program missions were contingent on the funding
Dialogue: 1,0:07:00.77,0:07:06.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,每年大约能从国会那讨来4.5亿美元的资金支持
Dialogue: 2,0:07:00.77,0:07:06.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,which was around $450 Million per year being supported by congress
Dialogue: 1,0:07:06.08,0:07:11.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,为了让国会满意 NASA必须在不出"重大问题"的情况下完成他们的计划
Dialogue: 2,0:07:06.08,0:07:11.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,and to keep congress happy NASA have to deliver on what they had planned with no major hitches.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:12.16,0:07:19.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,这个"重大问题"于1967年1月27日 在阿波罗一号上发生了
Dialogue: 2,0:07:12.16,0:07:19.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is where a massive spanner was thrown into the works with the Apollo 1 fire on January 27th, 1967
Dialogue: 1,0:07:19.94,0:07:26.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,宇航员维吉尔·格里森、爱德华·怀特与罗杰·查菲在一次"拔除插头"测试中丧生
Dialogue: 2,0:07:19.94,0:07:26.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,which claimed the lives of astronauts “Gus” Grissom, Ed White, and Roger Chaffee during a plugs-out test,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:26.54,0:07:30.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,本质上是火箭不加燃料的一次模拟发射演练
Dialogue: 2,0:07:26.54,0:07:30.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,basically a full simulation test of a launch but without fuel in the rocket.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:30.72,0:07:35.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,这对阿波罗计划是一个巨大的打击 导致了整个计划的重大改革
Dialogue: 2,0:07:30.72,0:07:35.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,This was a huge blow to Apollo and would lead to a major overhaul of the whole program
Dialogue: 1,0:07:35.84,0:07:39.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,但有人认为这也算是某种因祸得福
Dialogue: 2,0:07:35.84,0:07:39.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,but some say that it was a blessing in disguise.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:39.52,0:07:44.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,其原因是NASA一直在争分夺秒地遵守在60年代末将人类送上月球的最后期限
Dialogue: 2,0:07:39.52,0:07:44.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,The reasoning behind this was that NASA had been racing to keep to the deadline
Dialogue: 1,0:07:44.53,0:07:47.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,其原因是NASA一直在争分夺秒地遵守在60年代末将人类送上月球的最后期限
Dialogue: 2,0:07:44.53,0:07:47.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,of putting a man on the moon by the end of the 1960s
Dialogue: 1,0:07:47.72,0:07:53.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,并采取了某些所谓"不可接受的风险"以节省开支和成本
Dialogue: 2,0:07:47.72,0:07:53.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,and had taken what some say were unacceptable risks to cut corners and costs.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:54.08,0:07:57.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,阿波罗1号指令舱是早期的设计型号
Dialogue: 2,0:07:54.08,0:07:57.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Apollo 1 Command Module was an early design
Dialogue: 1,0:07:57.37,0:08:03.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,依赖于在太空中保持内部低压纯氧环境以节省重量和复杂性
Dialogue: 2,0:07:57.37,0:08:03.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,that relied upon a low-pressure pure oxygen environment in space to save weight and complexity
Dialogue: 1,0:08:03.90,0:08:08.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,而不是像我们在地球上呼吸的氮氧混合的空气
Dialogue: 2,0:08:03.90,0:08:08.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,compared to a nitrogen/oxygen mix more like we breathe on earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:08.88,0:08:12.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,舱门也被设计成向内打开
Dialogue: 2,0:08:08.88,0:08:12.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,The hatch door was also designed to open inwards,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:12.19,0:08:15.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,因此当火灾发生时 舱内的压力增加
Dialogue: 2,0:08:12.19,0:08:15.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,so when the fire took hold the pressure in the cabin increased
Dialogue: 1,0:08:15.80,0:08:19.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,三名宇航员无法从内部打开舱门
Dialogue: 2,0:08:15.80,0:08:19.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,making it impossible for the crew to open the door from the inside.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:20.08,0:08:24.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,水星和双子座任务也使用了纯氧环境
Dialogue: 2,0:08:20.08,0:08:24.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Mercury and Gemini missions also used a pure oxygen environment
Dialogue: 1,0:08:24.84,0:08:28.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,有人认为之前用着好好的
Dialogue: 2,0:08:24.84,0:08:28.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,and there was the thinking that because there had been no issues there
Dialogue: 1,0:08:28.07,0:08:31.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,那同样的纯氧舱内环境放到阿波罗上肯定也不会出问题
Dialogue: 2,0:08:28.07,0:08:31.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,then the same pure oxygen environment would work for Apollo,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:31.72,0:08:37.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,尽管设计要复杂得多 风险也大得多
Dialogue: 2,0:08:31.72,0:08:37.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,even though it was a much more complicated design and the risks were considerably greater.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:37.52,0:08:41.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,对航天工业的一些人来说 这是一个事故隐患
Dialogue: 2,0:08:37.52,0:08:41.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,To some in the space industry, this was an accident waiting to happen
Dialogue: 1,0:08:41.82,0:08:48.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果阿波罗1号测试成功 并且该计划继续采用这种原始设计
Dialogue: 2,0:08:41.82,0:08:48.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that if the Apollo 1 test had worked and the program had gone ahead with this original design,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:48.28,0:08:52.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,那这种事故很可能会在真正的发射中发生 导致人箭俱损
Dialogue: 2,0:08:48.28,0:08:52.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,this kind of accident would probably have happened during a real launch
Dialogue: 1,0:08:52.47,0:08:55.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,那这种事故很可能会在真正的发射中发生 导致人箭俱损
Dialogue: 2,0:08:52.47,0:08:55.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,with the subsequent loss of the crew and vehicle.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:56.08,0:09:00.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,从这个角度来看 如果真发生这种事故
Dialogue: 2,0:08:56.08,0:09:00.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,From that standpoint, it would have been much harder if not impossible
Dialogue: 1,0:09:00.26,0:09:05.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,在太空还不太可能找到原因 那阿波罗计划可能直接就被毙了
Dialogue: 2,0:09:00.26,0:09:05.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,to try and find the root cause of the exit and could well have ended the program there and then.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:05.76,0:09:11.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,事实上 我们仍然不知道具体是什么引发了阿波罗1号指令舱的火灾
Dialogue: 2,0:09:05.76,0:09:11.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,In fact, we still don't know exactly what triggered the fire in the Command Module of Apollo 1
Dialogue: 1,0:09:11.47,0:09:16.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,只有所谓"最可能"的原因 即一束短路的电线
Dialogue: 2,0:09:11.47,0:09:16.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,apart from the "most" likely cause was a short circuit in a bundle of wires.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:17.24,0:09:22.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,值得庆幸的是事故发生在测试期间 飞船就在发射台上
Dialogue: 2,0:09:17.24,0:09:22.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,One saving grace was that it happened during a test when it was on the launchpad
Dialogue: 1,0:09:22.40,0:09:28.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以指令舱仍然完好无损 可以对细节进行严格的取证
Dialogue: 2,0:09:22.40,0:09:28.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,so the Command Module was still intact and could be gone over in exacting forensic detail.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:28.48,0:09:31.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,这场火灾将项目推迟了21个月
Dialogue: 2,0:09:28.48,0:09:31.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,The fire delayed the program for 21 months
Dialogue: 1,0:09:31.62,0:09:36.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,在此期间 指令舱和其他系统进行了重大的设计更新
Dialogue: 2,0:09:31.62,0:09:36.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,in which time there was a major redesign of the Command Module and other systems
Dialogue: 1,0:09:36.33,0:09:39.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,并调整了NASA的工作方法
Dialogue: 2,0:09:36.33,0:09:39.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,and a shake-up of NASA's working practices
Dialogue: 1,0:09:39.26,0:09:44.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,更加强调安全 尤其是消防安全
Dialogue: 2,0:09:39.26,0:09:44.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,that had a much greater emphasis on safety and fire in particular.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:44.62,0:09:49.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,但所有这一切都发生在越南战争成本上升的同时
Dialogue: 2,0:09:44.62,0:09:49.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,But all this came at the same time as the cost of the Vietnam war was spiralled upwards
Dialogue: 1,0:09:49.84,0:09:55.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,林登·约翰逊想推出他的版本的罗斯福新政
Dialogue: 2,0:09:49.84,0:09:55.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,and President Lyndon Johnson wanted to introduce his version of Roosevelt's New Deal
Dialogue: 1,0:09:55.01,0:09:57.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,政策名为"伟大社会"
Dialogue: 2,0:09:55.01,0:09:57.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,called the Great Society,
Dialogue: 1,0:09:57.08,0:10:04.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,一套通过消除贫困和种族不公正来平息民间动乱的国内计划
Dialogue: 2,0:09:57.08,0:10:04.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,a set of domestic programs to quell civil unrest by eliminating poverty and racial injustice
Dialogue: 1,0:10:04.05,0:10:07.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,预算保持在1000亿美元内
Dialogue: 2,0:10:04.05,0:10:07.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,and keep within a $100 billion budget.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:08.32,0:10:10.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,由于所有这些利益的相互竞争
Dialogue: 2,0:10:08.32,0:10:10.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,With all these competing interests
Dialogue: 1,0:10:10.43,0:10:14.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,以及国会对NASA在阿波罗1号大火中的表现感到不满
Dialogue: 2,0:10:10.43,0:10:14.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,and congress's displeasure with NASA's performance around the Apollo 1 fire,
Dialogue: 1,0:10:14.71,0:10:17.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,阿波罗项目在削减预算的名单中首当其冲
Dialogue: 2,0:10:14.71,0:10:17.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,it meant that it was on the top of the list for budget cuts.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:18.13,0:10:20.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,国会不能把整个计划砍掉
Dialogue: 2,0:10:18.13,0:10:20.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,They couldn't cut the whole program
Dialogue: 1,0:10:20.14,0:10:25.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为这样会违背肯尼迪总统在1961年作出的承诺
Dialogue: 2,0:10:20.14,0:10:25.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,because that would renege of the promise that President Kennedy had made in 1961
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.12,0:10:37.96,辉注,,0,730,1005,,{\fs60}登月舱中继实验室
Dialogue: 1,0:10:25.06,0:10:30.08,辉中,,0,0,110,,但他们可以通过预算从4.5亿美元砍到1.22亿美元来浇灭"后阿波罗应用计划"
Dialogue: 2,0:10:25.06,0:10:30.08,辉英,,0,0,80,,but what they could do was to put a halt to the post-Apollo Applications Program
Dialogue: 1,0:10:30.08,0:10:35.61,辉中,,0,0,110,,但他们可以通过预算从4.5亿美元砍到1.22亿美元来浇灭"后阿波罗应用计划"
Dialogue: 2,0:10:30.08,0:10:35.61,辉英,,0,0,80,,by cutting by effectively cutting its budget from $450 Million to $122 million,
Dialogue: 1,0:10:35.61,0:10:39.29,辉中,,0,0,110,,这样的削减持续到了1970年尼克松总统时期
Dialogue: 2,0:10:35.61,0:10:39.29,辉英,,0,0,80,,a slide which continued under President Nixon in 1970.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.30,0:10:54.76,辉注,,0,330,960,,{\fs60}天空实验室是阿波罗应用计划中少有的生产出来的成品
Dialogue: 1,0:10:39.87,0:10:46.00,辉中,,0,0,170,,原定的阿波罗20号取消 其土星火箭被重新指派发射天体实验室
Dialogue: 2,0:10:39.87,0:10:46.00,辉英,,0,0,140,,The scheduled Apollo 20 was cancelled and its Saturn was redesignated to launch Skylab
Dialogue: 1,0:10:46.11,0:10:49.58,辉中,,0,0,170,,成为NASA"后阿波罗时期"计划的重点
Dialogue: 2,0:10:46.11,0:10:49.58,辉英,,0,0,140,,which would become the focus for NASA's post-Apollo plan
Dialogue: 1,0:10:49.58,0:10:55.71,辉中,,0,0,170,,直到航天飞机在1979年投入使用 虽然最后推迟到了1981年
Dialogue: 2,0:10:49.58,0:10:55.71,辉英,,0,0,140,,until the Space shuttle was meant to come into service in 1979, though that eventually turned into 1981.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:55.87,0:11:00.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,由于月球轨道勘测被取消
Dialogue: 2,0:10:55.87,0:11:00.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,Further reductions came as the Lunar orbital survey was cancelled
Dialogue: 1,0:11:00.02,0:11:05.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,登月任务也因阿波罗18号和19号被取消而缩短
Dialogue: 2,0:11:00.02,0:11:05.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the moon missions were cut short with the cancellation of Apollo 18 and 19
Dialogue: 1,0:11:05.10,0:11:11.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,导致阿波罗17号变成了第六次 也是最后一次阿波罗载人登月任务
Dialogue: 2,0:11:05.10,0:11:11.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,leaving Apollo 17 as the 6th and last Apollo manned mission to the moon.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:11.52,0:11:17.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,还有两枚土星火箭被用于随后的天空实验室任务和阿波罗-联盟对接任务
Dialogue: 2,0:11:11.52,0:11:17.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,Two more Saturn rockets were used on the following Skylab missions and one on the Apollo Soyuz mission
Dialogue: 1,0:11:17.67,0:11:25.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,1975年美国的阿波罗飞船指令舱与服务舱 同苏联的联盟号飞船对接
Dialogue: 2,0:11:17.67,0:11:25.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,where the American Apollo Command and Service Module docked with the Soviet Soyuz capsule in 1975
Dialogue: 1,0:11:25.18,0:11:27.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,两国宇航员在太空的这次握手
Dialogue: 2,0:11:25.18,0:11:27.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the handshake between the two crews
Dialogue: 1,0:11:27.65,0:11:35.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,似乎为18年前由苏联人造卫星1号的发射而开启的太空竞赛画上了圆满的句号
Dialogue: 2,0:11:27.65,0:11:35.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,seemed a fitting end to the Space race which began 18 years earlier with the launch of the Soviet Sputnik 1. 
